    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bottles or other glass vessels having the neck divided into two or more tubes, causing them to make a gurgling noise when poured. The type has Roman antecedents; it was notably produced by German glassworkers in the later Middle Ages, and among Venetian and façon de Venise glasses of the 16th and 17th centuries.</Note_Text>
